Helb should not force unemployed graduates who default on their loans to pay interest, a Nairobi woman representative hopeful has said.Millicent Omanga yesterday said the four per cent interest should only be levied on employed graduates. She spoke during a meeting with youths. Why should a person who is not working be charged interest? she said. Omanga said she is focused on empowering the youth and urged them to shun drugs and alcohol. She said she will ensure women and youth have a special place in her administration if elected.